### Blockers and bummers
 -  TLV consumers (bro, `HUNKu8sRelay`, any `be --tlv` tooling) must keep parsing `H` records â€” the wire shape is preserved (header sub-records stay optional), but `bro` rendering of the now-always-content hunks needs a check; the `T`/`V` banner-only hunk shape disappears, so any consumer special-casing it must migrate.
 -  Per-module flush timing vs. the relay: a parent that emits late rows AFTER a child hunk would interleave wrong â€” St.2 must flush the parent's own table before `BERelaySub`/the sub fork, not after.
 -  Links resolving: `U`-tok nav uris must resolve in bro (`cat:`/`blob:`/`diff:`/`commit:?<sha>`); the commit-range banners (`keeper/WALK.c`) currently carry the sha in `uri.query`+subject in `.fragment` (no `U` link) â€” St.2 must add the `commit:?<sha>` `U`-tok per [COMMIT-001] so range rows become clickable.
 -  [BLAME-005] blob/blame color-path inconsistency: the content renderer's no-toks fallback (`HUNKu8sFeedColor` `:584`) emits verbatim while the toks path paints per-span â€” the rework should make blob/blame highlight consistently; coordinate so BLAME-005's producer half lands against the unified renderer.
 -  Behavioral change (streamingâ†’batched) may surface in any test asserting incremental per-line output ordering; audit get/post tests in St.2.

